All Implemented Interfaces:
Transportable, ModbusMessage
public final class WriteMultipleRegistersRequest
extends ModbusRequest

Class implementing a WriteMultipleRegistersRequest. The implementation directly correlates with the class 0 function write multiple registers (FC 16). It encapsulates the corresponding request message.

Version:
1.2rc1 (09/11/2004), @version@ (@date@)
Author:
Dieter Wimberger, jfhaugh

getResponse

public ModbusResponse getResponse()
Description copied from class: ModbusRequest
Returns the ModbusResponse that correlates with this ModbusRequest.

The response must include the unit number, function code, as well as any transport-specific header information.

This method is used to create an empty response which must be populated by the caller. It is commonly used to un-marshal responses from Modbus slaves.

Specified by:
getResponse in class ModbusRequest
Returns:
the corresponding ModbusResponse.

createResponse

public ModbusResponse createResponse()
createResponse() must be able to handle the case where the word data that is in the response is actually non-word data. That is, where the slave device has data which are not actually short values in the range of registers being processed.
